Swinge 
===Etymology===
From {{OE.}} [[swengan]]: to shatter to {{ME.}} [[swenge]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|swinge|swinges|swinged|swingeing}}
#(Archaic) to strike hard.
#(Archaic) to [[lash]]
#(Obsolete) to [[singe]]*

====Usage note====
The meaning ''singe'' may be a spelling error on the part of Sir Edmund Spencer.

===Adjective===
# forcible, huge, daunting (of taxation, job-cuts, damages etc)

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
#(Archaic) a [[swing]]ing blow.